; tests/now-unix-ms-band.fk — sibling-witness band for the now_unix_ms native.
;
; preludes:
;
; (No preludes — the band uses only int primitives and the
; now_unix_ms native, both kernel-resident.)
;
; The clock native that closes the freshness gap. Every richer
; freshness walk (token expiry, ping stamps, heartbeat aging, async
; correlation windows) needs a sibling-aligned "right now" reading.
; This band attests that three sibling kernels (Go, Rust, TypeScript)
; each register the same native with the same SHAPE — even though
; the VALUE each kernel returns must differ (every kernel reads its
; own host clock at its own instant of invocation).
;
; Sibling parity therefore CAN'T check the exact value. It checks
; the SHAPE:
;
;   1. (now_unix_ms) returns a positive int.
;   2. (now_unix_ms) returns an int greater than a recent past epoch.
;
; Both checks land 1 on every kernel whose host clock is set sanely.
; The verdict is the sum of these booleans, which IS sibling-stable
; because every kernel sees the same booleans (1+1+1+1 = 4) — the
; underlying timestamp ints are NOT printed and NOT compared.
;
; The epoch threshold (1700000000000 = 2023-11-14T22:13:20.000Z) is
; chosen well before the band's authoring date but well after any
; uninitialized-RTC fallback (which typically resets to 0 or
; 1970-01-01), so a broken host fails the epoch check while still
; passing the positivity check — the band detects which failure mode
; without divergence between kernels.
;
; Costs: two native invocations, four integer comparisons, three
; adds. The walk fits inside the kernel's interpreter loop without
; any allocation. The Form→host JIT (when it lands) will compile
; this band to a few host instructions per clock read.

(do
    (let t1 (now_unix_ms))
    (let t2 (now_unix_ms))

    (let epoch 1700000000000)

    (let t1-positive (if (gt t1 0) 1 0))
    (let t2-positive (if (gt t2 0) 1 0))
    (let t1-after-epoch (if (gt t1 epoch) 1 0))
    (let t2-after-epoch (if (gt t2 epoch) 1 0))

    ;; Band verdict: 4 = two positivity checks + two epoch checks.
    ;; Every kernel reads its own clock; the VALUE diverges between
    ;; kernels but the BOOLEAN doesn't, so the sum is sibling-stable.
    (add t1-positive
         (add t2-positive
              (add t1-after-epoch t2-after-epoch))))
